<section id="community">
  <div class="sh"><div class="sh-n">07</div><div class="sh-t">Open source — extend to any destination</div></div>
  <div class="community-wrap">
    <div class="community-inner">
      <div>
        <h2 class="comm-h">The adapter SDK<br />ships with the repo.<br /><em>Build anything.</em></h2>
        <p class="comm-p">The Strategy interface is three methods. The adapter SDK gives you the types, the testing harness, the reference implementations, and the CF environment helpers. If your destination takes an HTTP request, you can write a strategy for it in an afternoon.</p>
        <p class="comm-p"><strong>Every merged community strategy ships free to every Attestrack deployment.</strong> No approval gate beyond a code review. No revenue share. No license restrictions. You build it, it ships to everyone, everyone benefits.</p>
        <p class="comm-p">The strategy manifest format is the same as the Attestrue marketplace format. Strategies built for Attestrack can be submitted to the Attestrue marketplace — and marketplace strategies verified by Attestrue's signing service can run in licensed deployments with independent evidence chain support.</p>
        <div class="comm-btns">
          <a href="https://github.com/attestrue/attestrue" class="btn-paper">View on GitHub &rarr;</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/attestrue/attestrue/blob/main/ADAPTER-DEVELOPMENT-GUIDE.md" class="btn-ghost">Adapter development guide &rarr;</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="wanted-label">Community strategies — wanted</div>
        <div class="contrib-grid">
          <div class="contrib-item"><div class="ci-mark">&rarr;</div><div class="ci-body"><strong>Snowflake strategy</strong> — stream events directly to Snowflake streaming tables. Schema DDL included.</div></div>
          <div class="contrib-item"><div class="ci-mark">&rarr;</div><div class="ci-body"><strong>BigQuery strategy</strong> — stream to BigQuery Storage Write API. No GCS intermediate.</div></div>
          <div class="contrib-item"><div class="ci-mark">&rarr;</div><div class="ci-body"><strong>Amplitude strategy</strong> — server-side events to Amplitude HTTP API v2.</div></div>
          <div class="contrib-item"><div class="ci-mark">&rarr;</div><div class="ci-body"><strong>PostHog strategy</strong> — self-hosted PostHog event capture server-side.</div></div>
          <div class="contrib-item"><div class="ci-mark">&rarr;</div><div class="ci-body"><strong>Klaviyo strategy</strong> — server-side identify and track events for email segmentation.</div></div>
          <div class="contrib-item"><div class="ci-mark">&rarr;</div><div class="ci-body"><strong>Snapchat / Pinterest / LinkedIn</strong> — Conversions APIs for the platforms that are not yet covered.</div></div>
          <div class="contrib-item"><div class="ci-mark">&rarr;</div><div class="ci-body"><strong>Any CDP</strong> — Segment, mParticle, RudderStack as a destination. Or as a source that pipes into Attestrack.</div></div>
        </div>
        <div class="sdk-note">The adapter SDK is at <code>packages/sdk</code>. The Strategy interface is three methods. The testing harness makes it easy to validate against mock events before submitting a PR.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

